text: No more revamps please- I would love to see more original content, new writers, and varying perspectives instead. There's more material out there if we stop writing from the same vantage point (young, 1st world, cisgender, etc.)  It's believed that Hollywood's rather heavy use of revamps lately is due to the already proven success of the original- so it's a (seemingly) safe financial bet to reintroduce this story to a newer generation. But how does the movie-going audience benefit from a drought of original and interesting cinema?  The audience doesn't really (we're entertained for a short period at most), so the benefits seem one-sided in favor of the studio. Look at the multitude and depreciating quality of Spiderman revamps and reboots- 6 movies in the past 15 years is unnecessary.
